               <history><origin><origPlace>Iceland</origPlace>
                  <origDate notBefore="1190" notAfter="1210" resp="ONP">c. 1200</origDate></origin>
                  <provenance>Fol. 1 and fol. 2 from <ref type="ms" target="AM04-0655-VIII-en">AM 655 VIII
                     4to</ref> were put into a paper cover on which 
                     <name type="person" key="ArnMag001">Árni Magnússon</name> wrote: <q xml:lang="is">Þetta gamla blad var lïmt ä spialld aptan vid latinſka Meſſu bok frä <name type="place" key="BærRey01">Saurbæ a Raudaſandi</name>, er eg feck <date when="1726">1726</date>. fra M<hi rend="sup">r</hi>
                        <name type="person" key="OrmDad001">Orme Dadaſyne</name>. Sieſt ſo hier af,
                        ad þeir elldri m<ex>enn</ex> hafa um þvilik<ex>ar</ex> gamlar lislendſkar
                        bækur vered älika hirdulauſer og vær. þvi banded ä þeſſarre
                        M<ex>esso</ex>bök, var ad viſu elldra (imò miklu elldra, ad eg hygg)
                        en<ex>n</ex> reformatio Lutheri, og hefur þä ecki ſtort vered hirdt um
                        peſſar fornu p<ex>re</ex>dikaner. Þo kynni <ex>og</ex> þetta þa
                        e<ex>ck</ex>i vered hafa nema fragment</q>.</provenance>
               </history>
